As temperatures drop across the Lowcountry, several warming shelters have opened to provide safe and warm environments for those in need. Here are the available options:

Holy City Missions Winter Warming Shelter at Aldersgate United Methodist Church
North Charleston, SC
Located at 1444 Remount Road, this shelter operates from 7 p.m. to 7 a.m. Guests receive a hot meal, breakfast, and access to showers. Men, women, and children are welcome; however, pets are not permitted. Transportation is available via CARTA bus route 13; passengers should request the Aldersgate Winter Warming Shelter stop. 
Seacoast Church Summerville Warming Center
Summerville, SC
Situated at 301 E. 5th North Street, with the entrance at the back door facing Gum Street, this center operates from 7 p.m. to 7 a.m. on designated nights. Guests are provided with a cot, warm dinner, to-go breakfast, and access to hot showers. While all are welcome, pets are not allowed. For transportation, CARTA buses have added a special stop on nights the center is open. Passengers should inform the driver if they need transport from the Charleston area to Summerville, as a transfer at Trident Hospital may be required. 

Hibben Hospitality Shelter
Mount Pleasant, SC
This shelter operates from 7 p.m. to 7 a.m. on designated nights, providing guests with a hot meal, breakfast, showers, and a change of clothes. Men, women, and children are welcome; pets are not allowed. Transportation details can be obtained by contacting local services. 

Goose Creek United Methodist Church Warming Center
Goose Creek, SC
Open from 7 p.m. to 7 a.m. on designated nights, this center offers a warm place to stay and meals. Men, women, and children are welcome; pets are not permitted. CARTA provides transportation to this location; passengers should check the latest schedules and stops. 

For the most current information on shelter availability and operating hours, it's recommended to contact the shelters directly or consult local authorities. Transportation assistance is available through CARTA bus services, with specific routes and stops designated for each shelter. Passengers should inform drivers of their intended destination to ensure proper routing.
